          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy Ion Research Facility",
                "                of Lanzhou (HIRFL)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "FRAGM"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The secondary beams of radioactive isotopes",
                " were produced by the fragmentation of the 12C6+",
                " primary beam on a 9Be target with a thickness of 2652",
                " um using the HIRFL. The secondary beams 7Be, 8B, and",
                " 9C, were separated by magnetic rigidity and delivered",
                " by the Radioactive Ion Beam Line in Lanzhou (RIBLL).",
                " The beam intensities of 7Be, 8B, and 9C were",
                " 1.5E4 pps, 1.0E3 pps, and 5.0E2 pps, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The natural Pb target was a self-supporting foil with",
                " a thickness of 4.2 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The ToF was measured with two 50-um-thick",
                " plastic scintillators located on the second and",
                " fourth focal planes of the RIBLL."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The energy loss for each beam was measured with",
                " a 280-um-thick silicon detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS",
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two position-sensitive parallel-plate",
                " avalanche counters (PPACs), with a position",
                " resolution of 1 mm, were fixed in front of the natPb",
                " target, at distances of 100 and 500 mm, respectively.",
                " Each PPAC had 80 gold-plated tungsten wires as anode",
                " in both the X and the Y directions. The tungsten",
                " wires, 20 um in diameter, were spaced 1 mm apart,",
                " providing a sensitive area of 80 x 80 cm2."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two sets of delta E-E silicon",
                " telescopes, which consisted of a double-sided silicon",
                " strip detector (48 strips of 1 mm width, each",
                " including a 0.1 mm interval) with a thickness of 150",
                " um and a large surface silicon detector with a",
                " thickness of 1500 um. Each telescope covered a polar",
                " angle of 7-30 deg in the laboratory frame, on either",
                " side of the beam axis. The distances from the natPb",
                " target to the center of the telescopes were 247 and",
                " 201 mm, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDEG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 301-um-thick aluminum plate, located on the",
                " second focal plane of the RIBLL, was utilized to",
                " degrade the incident energy and to improve the purity",
                " of the secondary beams."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Secondary beams were identified using a",
                " time-of-flight and energy loss (ToF-Delta E)",
                " technique with a certain magnetic rigidity. Elastic",
                " scattering events were detected using two sets of",
                " delta E-E silicon telescopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
